{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Wrap potatoes in foil, place on a baking tray and bake for 45 minutes - 1 hour (180°C) until cooked. Meanwhile, place a large bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in soya mince. Remove from lid and cover with water then leave to soak.","Place mozzarella and Cheddar in mixing bowl then grate <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, onions, parsley, ginger, courgettes and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Heat <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add soaked and drained soya, chopped tomatoes, wine, soy sauce, salt and pepper then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add spinach and pine nuts then stir in well with spatula.","Increase oven temperature to 200°C.","Slice off tops of potatoes and scoop out filling leaving 1 cm around edges. Fill with stuffing then sprinkle with reserved grated cheese. Place in an oven-proof dish then bake for 10 minutes (200°C) or until golden. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["8 potatoes, medium sized (approx. 1350 g)","150 g soya mince (granules)","water, for soaking","100 g grated mozzarella","50 g Cheddar cheese (mature), cut in pieces (3 cm)","2 garlic cloves","120 g onions, quartered","10 g fresh parsley, leaves only","10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","150 g courgettes, cut in pieces","30 g olive oil","100 g tinned chopped tomatoes","50 g white wine","25 g soy sauce","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","70 g fresh spinach leaves","20 g pine nuts"]}],"id":"r134397","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-hqOftckTzsk\/XZVRg_urGJI\/AAAAAAAAdPY\/lBR8T7RKQ6QyR6d5tme9ILScvr9GbXHIgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_q9Y_PD6dS35Dhgae.png","title":"Potatoes Stuffed with Soya Mince, Spinach and Pine Nuts","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.9 g","fat":"10.9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"36.1 g","calories":"1314 kJ \/ 314 kcal"},"